{"answer": "John drives to his parents’ house in 2 hours at a constant speed of 70 mph.  
First, find the one‑way distance:

\[
\text{Distance}_{\text{one‑way}} = \text{speed} \times \text{time}
= 70\ \text{mph} \times 2\ \text{h}
\]

\[
\text{Distance}_{\text{one‑way}} = <<140>>\ \text{miles}
\]

The round trip is twice that distance:

\[
\text{Distance}_{\text{round trip}} = 2 \times \text{Distance}_{\text{one‑way}}
= 2 \times 140
\]

\[
\text{Distance}_{\text{round trip}} = <<280>>\ \text{miles}
\]

John makes this round trip twice each month, so the monthly mileage is:

\[
\text{Monthly mileage} = 2 \times \text{Distance}_{\text{round trip}}
= 2 \times 280
\]

\[
\text{Monthly mileage} = <<560>>\ \text{miles}
\]

#### 560 miles"}
